
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-templin-seal-23.txt'>
    <title>"The Subnetwork Encapsulation and Adaptation Layer (SEAL)", Fred Templin</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-templin-seal-23.txt</link>
    <description>For the purpose of this document, subnetworks are defined as virtual topologies that span connected network regions bounded by encapsulated border nodes.  These virtual topologies may span multiple IP- and/or sub-IP layer forwarding hops, and can introduce failure modes due to packet duplication and/or links with diverse Maximum Transmission Units (MTUs).  This document specifies a Subnetwork Encapsulation and Adaptation Layer (SEAL) that accommodates such virtual topologies over diverse underlying link technologies.</description>
    <dc:date>2008-08-18T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
